tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE network_outages (
	outage_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
	start_time TIMESTAMP,
	duration INTERVAL,
	location VARCHAR(255),
	severity ENUM('LOW', 'MEDIUM', 'HIGH'),
	incident_report TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE network_outages (
    outage_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    outage_start TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    outage_end TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    outage_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    outage_description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE network_outages (
  outage_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  outage_type VARCHAR(255),
  start_time TIMESTAMP,
  end_time TIMESTAMP,
  affected_network VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE failure_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  outage_id INT,
  failure_type VARCHAR(255),
  failure_description TEXT,
  analyst_name VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE incident_reports (
  report_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  outage_id INT,
  report_date DATE,
  report_details TEXT,
  reporter_name VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE network_equipment (
  equipment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  equipment_type VARCHAR(255),
  installation_date DATE,
  manufacturer VARCHAR(255),
  location VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE resolution_actions (
  action_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  outage_id INT,
  action_type VARCHAR(255),
  action_description TEXT,
  executor_name VARCHAR(255)
)
